&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Synovial fluid&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;color: (33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Synovial fluid&lt;/strong&gt; is a viscous fluid found in the cavities of synovial joints.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;It serves the purpose of &lt;strong&gt;lubricating&lt;/strong&gt; the joints, reducing friction between the articular cartilage of synovial joints during movement.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The fluid also plays a crucial role in &lt;strong&gt;nutrient distribution&lt;/strong&gt; and waste removal for the cartilage cells within the joint.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;This fluid is produced by the &lt;strong&gt;synovial membrane&lt;/strong&gt;, which lines the joint capsule.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;It also acts as a &lt;strong&gt;shock absorber&lt;/strong&gt;, cushioning the joints during activities such as walking, running, and jumping.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Amniotic fluid&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Amniotic fluid&lt;/strong&gt; surrounds a developing fetus during pregnancy.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It protects the fetus by cushioning against external pressure and trauma.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It helps in the development of the fetal lungs and digestive system.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Interstitial fluid&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Interstitial fluid&lt;/strong&gt; is found in the spaces between cells throughout the body.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It helps in the transport of nutrients, oxygen, and waste products to and from cells.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cerebrospinal fluid&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cerebrospinal fluid (CSF)&lt;/strong&gt; is found in the brain and spinal cord.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It acts as a cushion for the brain, providing protection against physical impacts.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;CSF also helps in the circulation of nutrients and removal of waste products from the brain.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;option 3&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;R21/Matrix-M&amp;trade; is a malaria vaccine developed by the University of Oxford and manufactured by Serum Institute of India (SII)&lt;/strong&gt; in collaboration with Novavax. &lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hence, option 3 is correct.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;It is an improved version of RTS,S/AS01 (the first malaria vaccine).&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The Matrix-M&amp;trade; component is an adjuvant developed by Novavax to enhance the immune response.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The vaccine has shown high efficacy (around 75%) in clinical trials and has been approved for use in several African countries.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The WHO approved this vaccine in 2023, marking a major step in malaria prevention.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Malaria:&lt;/strong&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cause:&lt;/strong&gt; Malaria is caused by Plasmodium parasites, with P. falciparum and P. vivax being the most common in humans.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Transmission:&lt;/strong&gt; It is spread through the bite of female Anopheles mosquitoes.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Symptoms: &lt;/strong&gt;Fever, chills, headache, nausea, muscle pain, and severe complications like organ failure in severe cases.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Global Impact:&lt;/strong&gt;
		&lt;ul&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;Malaria is a major public health issue, particularly in Africa, South Asia, and South America.&lt;/li&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;In 2021, the WHO reported approximately 247 million malaria cases worldwide, with 619,000 deaths.&lt;/li&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;Children under 5 and pregnant women are at the highest risk.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;/ul&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p data-end=&quot;75&quot; data-start=&quot;0&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Option 2&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

